value.0: Stocky and brawny like many duergar, this one seems to be a particularly mean specimen. Hair as black as coal covers his head, and he wears his beard short. Dusky gray skin and an avaricious gleam in his eyes are the only other notable features, aside from a wicked scar down the right side of his face, from temple to jaw. He's most often seen wearing his darkly colored platemail, which is emblazoned with the broken-bolt insignia of Laduguer above an insignia depicting a sword crossed with a hammer, surmounted by a black diamond.

Skinny and frail, this elderly deep gnome wears soft, dark robes the color of stone, and has a bulging belt-pouch. His bespectacled visage is creased with furrows, and he often stutters when he speaks. Below his long, somewhat crooked nose lies a thick moustache, obviously well-groomed. He often is seen to carry a staff set with a shining emerald on the top.

Large and strong, this Orog is clearly a believer in the saying "might makes right." His body is crisscrossed with scars and old wounds, and a massive sword is almost always strapped across his back. Strangely though, his armor is meticulously clean and well-cared for. He has a deep voice, with a grating quality to it when he speaks, though his speech indicates quite clearly he's a brute with brains. Across his arms can be seen numerous tattoos, apparently of a tribal nature.

Slender and dextrous, though fairly short at a few inches under 5 foot, this drow male possesses the fine features that strongly hint at noble bloodlines. Ruby-red eyes gleam in a face black as obsidian, and his lips usually bear a charming smile. His snugly-fitting clothing is richly decorated with gems and precious metals, as are the thinblade and flute belted at his hips. He proudly bears a cloak clasp formed into the crest of Clan Zau'tar. Everything on him, from his boots, to his clothing, to his elegant hairstyle, points to a high degree of wealth, sophistication, and style.

This towering (for a) Drowess often carries a faintly amused smirk on her face. Long hair decorated with black pearls frames beautiful obsidian features, as is normal for her race. Her red eyes often seem to show a hint of cruel amusement when she's speaking to someone, especially when twisting the verbal knife. In her hand is the snake whip common to higher ranking priestesses of the Spider Queen's faith.
